Río Churu - - Following the Río Churu from 200 m W. of Aguilani to 1 km above the main fork up river. 3 km SE of the ruins of Choquecamiri, 17 km N. of Choquetanga. Riverine woodlands and mattorals, often dominated by Acalypha in the deep canyon.

Río Isi Taxaña - - Following slope down through ancient agricultural terraces, newly discovered today, about 2 km up the Río Isi Taxaña (mis-labelled on map as Río Khenwani) from its junction with the Río Miguillas. 22 km N. of Choquetanga. Deciduous forest, mostly without leaves at present, Adelanthus, Acacia and Tabebuia common. Along the river the forest is evergreen and very diverse.
